    Guard I

    The ability to block melee attacks aimed at one person in close proximity. This ability is received upon specializing in Shields to level 5.
    Guard II

    An improved version of Guard that has a higher chance to block attacks. This ability is received upon specializing in Shields to level 10.
    Guard III

    An improved version of Guard that has a higher chance to block attacks. This ability is received upon specializing in Shields to level 15.
    Evade I

    The ability to evade blows from your opponent. This ability is completely passive and will begin to work as soon as you acquire it.
    Evade II

    Like Evade I, only you are better at it.
    Evade III

    Like Evade II, only you are better at it.
    Evade IV

    Like Evade III, only you are better at it.
    Evade V

    Like Evade IV, only you are better at it.
    Evade VI

    Like Evade V, only you are better at it.
    Evade VII

    Like the rest of the Evades... With this ability one could evade Death himself.
    Advanced Evade

    Certain classes have learned to evade attacks even when they cannot physically see their opponent. Advanced Evade allows evasion from attacks on you occurring from any direction.
    Celtic Dual
    ->Combat Style List

    The ability to effectively use two weapons in combat instead of one. This works only with one-handed weapons in Hibernia. The base chance to swing both weapons is 25%, and every time you train in Celtic Dual, your chance to swing both weapons is increased by .5%
    Dual Wield
    ->Combat Style List

    The ability to effectively use two weapons in combat instead of one. This works only with one-handed weapons in Albion. The base chance to swing both weapons is 25%, and every time you train in Dual Wield, your chance to swing both weapons is increased by .5%
    Left Axe
    ->Combat Style List

    Like Dual Wield, but only good with axes in Midgard. With Left Axe, you swing both weapons during every combat round, but your damage with those weapons is decreased.
    Berserk I

    This ability is native to the Berserker, and allows him to do more damage than would normally be possible by throwing himself into a berserker rage, transforming into a Vendo (BearPerson) during combat. Berserk makes every hit for a certain time a critical hit, but can only be used once every 7 minutes.
    Berserk II

    Like Berserk I, only better.
    Berserk III

    Like Berserk II, only better.
    Berserk IV

    You're a maniac, what else can I say? Baddies Beware!
    Spirit of the Hunt: Initiate

    This ability is Native to the Hero. He can shapeshift into a fearsome stag-headed Hunstman of Celtic Lore, once per 30 minutes, lasting 30 seconds. This level of Spirit of the Hunt grants a 20% hitpoint bonus.
    Spirit of the Hunt: Member

    This level of Spirit of the Hunt grants a 30% hitpoint bonus.
    Spirit of the Hunt: Leader

    This level of Spirit of the Hunt grants a 40% hitpoint bonus.
    Spirit of the Hunt: Master

    This level of Spirit of the Hunt grants a 50% hitpoint bonus.
    Dirty Tricks

    This ability is Native to the Mercenary. These hired hands will do anything to win a fight - including this dirty trick of throwing dirt into the enemy's eyes. For 30 seconds, the Mercenary has a chance of throwing dirt into the enemy's eyes whenever he swings. If hit, the enemy will miss 25% more often, and fumble 50% more often for 10 seconds. This ability can be used once per 7 minues.
    Triple Wield

    This ability is native to the Blademaster. These masters of the blade art have learned to summon a magic sword to fight with them for 30 seconds, once per 7 minutes. The magical sword damages the enemy every time the Blademaster hits, inflicting 50% of the damage of the swing, and protects the Blademaster from all critical hit damage during that 30 seconds.
    Critical Strike
    ->Combat Style List

    The Thief-Only skill dealing with backstabs and roguish maneuvers.
    Savagery
    ->Savagery List

    This skill is native to the Savage. Savagery is a set of spell-like abilities that modify the Savage's combat performance - chance to block, chance to evade, etc. However, unlike spells, the Savagery abilities cost Health and not Power.


    Miscellaneous Skills ~



    Stealth

    The ability to hide yourself in the surrounding landscape. The better you are at this, the closer you can come to an enemy without it detecting your presence. Assassins and Minstrels gain access to the Distract, Safefall, and Climb Walls abilities by speccing Stealth. Please read the FAQfor more information.
    Distract

    The ability to temporarily direct a monster's attention in a different direction.
    Climb Walls

    The ability to climb up certain points on frontier keep walls. Available to Minstrels and Assassins at 25 spec in Stealth.
    Safefall

    An automatic ability that partially reduces the damage from falling. Available to Ministrels and Assassins at 10 spec in stealth, with improved versions at 20, 30, 40, and 50.
    Envenom

    All thieves learn the Envenom skill at level 5. This allows them to apply poisons to their weapons before going into battle. Different poisons have different effects on your enemy -- some debuff, some apply a damage-over-time, etc. It is expected that a thief will always attack with an envenomed weapon, so make sure you stock up on poison before you head out hunting.
    Camouflage

    The purpose of Camouflage is for the Archer to be able to move about unseen, but not be able to use it to engage in stealthed combat. You use it just like any other ability - first, you must be stealthed, then click on the Camouflage icon to activate the ability. When you are Camouflaged, essentially you are invisible from the assassin See Hidden ability - however, you abide by all the rules of being stealthed normally; i.e. you have a greater chance of being visible to those that are higher level than yourself. You will move at your normal stealthed speed, and you will become visible if you engage in combat (take damage, attack someone, shoot someone with a bow, etc.).
    Flurry

    Once every two minutes, certain classes have the ability to add an instant attack to their normal melee, however, Flurry is only useable in RvR Combat.
    Charge

    When Charging, the tank sprints at full sprint speed, with no endurance loss, for 10 seconds towards the target. If he breaks off, or changes target, or the 10 seconds expires, the tank goes back to normal running speed. Can be used every 5 minutes.
    Sprint Ability

    The ability sprint, and for a short while, run faster than normal. This ability drains stamina very quickly. Every class in the game has this skill at level one, but each class also has varying degrees of stamina.




